<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-05-06T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-05-06T07:00:00-05:00" n="38" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15 a 1/216: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Houghton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-05-06T13:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 6, 1927—1
                                        p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 6—8:56
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>105. Your 93, May 5, noon. Chamberlain assures me that British delegation
                            at the forthcoming Three-Power Conference will include fully empowered
                            Dominion representatives.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Houghton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>